2247
01:51:13,500 --> 01:51:14,918
that if I hadn't
went through that,

2248
01:51:15,001 --> 01:51:16,878
I probably couldn't have
ministered to those families,

2249
01:51:16,961 --> 01:51:19,547
'cause I would've never
known that experience.

2250
01:51:19,631 --> 01:51:25,595
2020, we must deal
with police brutality.

2251
01:51:25,679 --> 01:51:28,723
2020, we must deal with those

2252
01:51:28,807 --> 01:51:32,060
that want to rob
our right to vote.

2253
01:51:32,143 --> 01:51:33,561
[applause]

2254
01:51:33,645 --> 01:51:36,564
[Sharpton]: So I know what
a lot of those families I end up

2255
01:51:36,648 --> 01:51:41,027
later in life had to go
through, 'cause I was that kid.

2256
01:51:41,111 --> 01:51:45,490
And I didn't come to
shame 'em or use 'em.

2257
01:51:45,573 --> 01:51:47,409
I came to help 'em

2258
01:51:47,492 --> 01:51:49,494
and help the cause.

2259
01:51:49,577 --> 01:51:53,540
I bring you the brother
of George Floyd,

2260
01:51:53,623 --> 01:51:55,458
Philonise Floyd.

2261
01:51:55,583 --> 01:51:59,587
But you can't ignore their
needs to help the cause.

2262
01:51:59,671 --> 01:52:03,258
And I never talk about
it, won't talk about it now.

2263
01:52:03,341 --> 01:52:05,635
That's between
me and the families.

2264
01:52:05,719 --> 01:52:07,637
It's part of that vow I made.

2265
01:52:07,721 --> 01:52:12,726
[Philonise]: I wish George
were here to see this right now.

2266
01:52:12,809 --> 01:52:15,687
That's who I'm marching for.

2267
01:52:15,770 --> 01:52:20,442
I'm marching for
George, for Breonna,

2268
01:52:20,525 --> 01:52:25,238
for Ahmaud, for Jacob,

2269
01:52:25,321 --> 01:52:30,493
for Michael Brown, Trayvon,

2270
01:52:30,577 --> 01:52:35,415
and anybody else
