2290
01:53:53,618 --> 01:53:57,914
- [Man]: Say his name!
- [Group]: George Floyd!

2291
01:53:59,040 --> 01:54:00,416
[Sharpton]: This
is the first time

2292
01:54:00,500 --> 01:54:01,876
in the history of this state

2293
01:54:01,960 --> 01:54:06,506
that a white police officer has
been convicted of a murder.

2294
01:54:07,173 --> 01:54:11,719
This is the first time
in a long ray of fights

2295
01:54:11,803 --> 01:54:17,892
that we've seen three
counts guilty in all three.

2296
01:54:17,976 --> 01:54:20,770
We don't find pleasure in this.

2297
01:54:20,854 --> 01:54:23,481
The war and the
fight is not over.

2298
01:54:23,565 --> 01:54:24,732
Just two days from now,

2299
01:54:24,816 --> 01:54:27,485
we're going to have to
deal with the funeral of

2300
01:54:27,569 --> 01:54:31,239
Daunte Wright in this same area.

2301
01:54:31,322 --> 01:54:36,077
Before we do anything,
we first wanna pray.

2302
01:54:36,160 --> 01:54:39,831
We believe in a God that can
even get through the cracks

2303
01:54:39,914 --> 01:54:45,378
of the jury room and bring
conscious and bring truth.

2304
01:54:45,461 --> 01:54:47,755
And that jury, we
wanna thank them

2305
01:54:47,839 --> 01:54:50,717
for letting God give
them the strength.

2306
01:54:50,800 --> 01:54:53,261
Wherever they are tonight,
we want them to know

2307
01:54:53,344 --> 01:54:57,682
we broke down in tears
when we heard the verdict.

2308
01:54:57,765 --> 01:55:00,685
We had to hold each
other and hug and tears,

2309
01:55:00,768 --> 01:55:02,937
because too many
nights we've cried,

2310
01:55:03,021 --> 01:55:06,816
many of us for decades,
spent nights in jail.

2311
01:55:06,900 --> 01:55:09,736
But today we can
wipe our tears away

2312
01:55:09,819 --> 01:55:11,529
and fight on for another day.

2313
01:55:11,613 --> 01:55:12,947
There's sunlight.

2314
01:55:13,031 --> 01:55:16,284
We're gonna keep going 'til
we bring it for the Eric Gardners

2315
01:55:16,367 --> 01:55:19,454
and the Breonna Taylors,
whose boyfriend is here tonight.

2316
01:55:19,537 --> 01:55:20,246
[Man]: Kenny Walker.

2317
01:55:20,330 --> 01:55:21,205
Kenny Walker.

2318
01:55:21,289 --> 01:55:22,332
[applause]

2319
01:55:22,415 --> 01:55:26,377
Sean Bell, so many
that did not get this night,

2320
01:55:26,461 --> 01:55:27,587
this night is for them.

2321
01:55:27,670 --> 01:55:29,505
Let us pray.

2322
01:55:31,090 --> 01:55:32,300
What about the meeting?

2323
01:55:32,383 --> 01:55:33,927
{\an8}Are you satisfied with
what went on in there?

2324
01:55:34,010 --> 01:55:35,511
{\an8}We asked the police
commissioner point blank

2325
01:55:35,595 --> 01:55:38,806
{\an8}to suspend--
emphatically suspend

2326
01:55:38,890 --> 01:55:39,891
{\an8}the officer in question.

2327
01:55:39,974 --> 01:55:43,561
{\an8}And we got a lot of
runaround about that.

2328
01:55:43,645 --> 01:55:45,855
{\an8}[Sharpton]: Dear
God, we thank you

2329
01:55:45,939 --> 01:55:49,108
for giving us the
strength to stand together.

2330
01:55:49,192 --> 01:55:51,903
Sometimes we would
question each other.

2331
01:55:51,986 --> 01:55:55,281
Sometimes we say this is
just gonna be a waste of time.

2332
01:55:55,365 --> 01:55:58,409
A young man was shot and his
murderer has not been punished.

2333
01:55:58,493 --> 01:56:01,245
And, I mean, you can talk
about long range, short range,

2334
01:56:01,329 --> 01:56:03,748
any kind of
investigations you want.

2335
01:56:03,831 --> 01:56:06,542
[Sharpton]: And
Lord, let George know

2336
01:56:06,626 --> 01:56:09,420
that his name is
going down in history.

2337
01:56:09,504 --> 01:56:10,922
And we give you the praise.

2338
01:56:11,005 --> 01:56:14,759
Thank you, and God,
we give you the glory.

2339
01:56:14,842 --> 01:56:17,971
These blessings we
ask in your name, amen.

2340
01:56:18,054 --> 01:56:19,681
[All]: Amen!

2341
01:56:19,764 --> 01:56:20,890
Amen!

2342
01:56:20,974 --> 01:56:22,058
[applause]

2343
01:56:22,141 --> 01:56:23,768
[Sharpton]: You
have white policemen

2344
01:56:23,851 --> 01:56:25,812
policing the community
that have the same mentality

2345
01:56:25,895 --> 01:56:27,063
that this man has.

2346
01:56:27,146 --> 01:56:28,815
So, I mean, you're
talking about the grand jury

2347
01:56:28,898 --> 01:56:30,692
and an investigation, a
DA, means nothing to us.

2348
01:56:30,775 --> 01:56:32,318
The only thing that
means something to us

2349
01:56:32,402 --> 01:56:33,528
is direct action--

2350
01:56:33,611 --> 01:56:37,532
pull the white policeman out
and deal with that situation.

2351
01:56:38,783 --> 01:56:39,909
Reverend Alfred Sharpton,

2352
01:56:39,993 --> 01:56:41,452
chairman of the National
Youth Movement.

2353
01:56:41,536 --> 01:56:43,788
{\an8}[Terrence Floyd]: Reverend
Jesse Jackson and Al Sharpton,

2354
01:56:43,871 --> 01:56:45,707
{\an8}they lived to see this.

2355
01:56:47,834 --> 01:56:50,086
{\an8}Their fight wasn't in vain.

2356
01:56:50,712 --> 01:56:53,006
{\an8}It just didn't happen
when they did it.

2357
01:56:53,089 --> 01:56:54,215
{\an8}But it happened now.

2358
01:56:54,298 --> 01:56:57,093
{\an8}Let's make sure, Reverend
Al, that this moment

2359
01:56:57,176 --> 01:57:02,807
{\an8}will be documented for
our children yet unborn

2360
01:57:03,516 --> 01:57:08,688
{\an8}as they continue on
the journey to justice.

2361
01:57:08,771 --> 01:57:10,857
{\an8}[Sharpton]: I never
thought I would see

2362
01:57:10,940 --> 01:57:13,943
a policeman convicted
on all three charges.

2363
01:57:14,027 --> 01:57:15,695
Movements need victories.

2364
01:57:15,778 --> 01:57:17,989
The George Floyd
verdict gave us that victory.

2365
01:57:18,072 --> 01:57:19,741
[Female reporter]:
Congratulations. Thank you so much.

2366
01:57:19,824 --> 01:57:22,493
[Sharpton]: When I
started at 18 years old

2367
01:57:22,577 --> 01:57:23,703
as a youth director for

2368
01:57:23,786 --> 01:57:26,205
Shirley Chisolm
for President in '72,

2369
01:57:26,289 --> 01:57:30,293
we never dreamed of a Black
woman being vice president.

2370
01:57:31,210 --> 01:57:33,838
When we would boycott and picket

2371
01:57:33,921 --> 01:57:36,466
supermarkets and
stores in my teen years

2372
01:57:36,549 --> 01:57:38,051
in Operation Breadbasket,

2373
01:57:38,134 --> 01:57:42,722
it was not even in
the realm of fantasy

2374
01:57:42,805 --> 01:57:47,143
that we'd see Black CEOs
of Fortune 500 companies.

2375
01:57:47,226 --> 01:57:49,854
Don't tell me
things won't change.

2376
01:57:49,937 --> 01:57:53,357
I kept telling family after
family that we keep going,

2377
01:57:53,441 --> 01:57:56,110
at some point,
we'll break through.

2378
01:57:56,194 --> 01:58:01,074
I sat on the stage when a Black
man named Barack Hussein Obama

2379
01:58:01,157 --> 01:58:05,286
put his hand on Abraham Lincoln
and Martin Luther King's bible

2380
01:58:05,369 --> 01:58:07,622
and was sworn in president
of the United States.

2381
01:58:07,705 --> 01:58:13,419
I've seen too much change
to feel that nothing will change.

2382
01:58:15,838 --> 01:58:18,925
I've seen a lot of
things go backwards,

2383
01:58:19,008 --> 01:58:23,137
but I keep the change in my
head because the change I've seen

2384
01:58:23,221 --> 01:58:28,017
makes me know that if we keep
going, we can break through.

2385
01:58:28,101 --> 01:58:33,397
I want to use for a subject,
"No Justice, No Peace."

2386
01:58:33,481 --> 01:58:35,316
[applause]

2387
01:58:35,399 --> 01:58:39,278
I want 50, 100 years from
now for somebody to say,

2388
01:58:39,362 --> 01:58:44,158
there was a time police
used to get way with brutality.

2389
01:58:44,242 --> 01:58:47,578
There was a time that they
gave a Voting Rights Act,

2390
01:58:47,662 --> 01:58:48,871
and it lasted 50 years,

2391
01:58:48,955 --> 01:58:51,374
and the Supreme Court
took the gut out of it.

2392
01:58:51,457 --> 01:58:54,252
And oh, there was a
little fat guy from Brooklyn

2393
01:58:54,335 --> 01:58:55,795
who dropped out of college.

2394
01:58:55,878 --> 01:58:58,005
When he got older,
he lost the weight.

2395
01:58:58,089 --> 01:59:00,925
He was on the front
line to help in all of that.

2396
01:59:01,008 --> 01:59:02,760
Nobody will care what
kind of apartment I have.

2397
01:59:02,844 --> 01:59:04,929
Nobody will care how
much money I made.

2398
01:59:05,012 --> 01:59:07,181
They'll care that I
was one of them.

2399
01:59:07,265 --> 01:59:10,560
Did those two or
three things in history.

2400
01:59:10,643 --> 01:59:13,312
That's all. That's all.

2401
01:59:13,396 --> 01:59:17,733
And when I see my mentors
in heaven, I can tell them...

2402
01:59:17,817 --> 01:59:20,194
I got some stuff done.

2403
